.:: Puzzle 1x6-Level-8-6::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: motorbike, train, quad-bike, bus, tram, jet-ski
1. the person driving the motorbike is somewhere between the person driving the quad-bike and the person driving the train##7
2. the person driving the jet-ski is not to the right of the person driving the train##8
3. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left or right of the person driving the bus##3
4. the person driving the bus is in an odd position##4
5. the person driving the train is on the left of the person driving the tram##1
6. the person driving the jet-ski is somewhere to the left of the person driving the bus##5
7. the person driving the train is somewhere to the right of the person driving the quad-bike##5
8. the person driving the bus is somewhere between the person driving the quad-bike and the person driving the motorbike##7

.:: Answer ::.
|       |   1   |   2    |   3    |     4      |    5     |  6  |
| Transport   | jet-ski | quad-bike | bus | motorbike | train | tram |

