.:: Puzzle 1x6-Level-8-8::.
6 different games are played: snooker, bridge, mah-jongg, billiard, backgammon, go
1. the person playing billiard is on the left or right of the person playing go##3
2. the person playing backgammon is somewhere between the person playing mah-jongg and the person playing billiard##7
3. the person playing billiard is on the left of the person playing go##1
4. the person playing billiard is not to the left of the person playing snooker##8
5. the person playing snooker is not to the left of the person playing mah-jongg##8
6. the person playing snooker is on the right of the person playing bridge##1
7. the person playing backgammon is between the person playing bridge and the person playing mah-jongg##2
8. the person playing mah-jongg is somewhere to the left of the person playing snooker##5

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1    |    2     |    3    |    4     |   5    |     6      |
| Game   | mah-jongg | backgammon | bridge | snooker | billiard | go |

